# Preem Palver · the farmer who was First Speaker

a persona of the A1 (Asimov) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** A stout, balding, comfortable-looking man with the manner of a Trantorian dirt-farmer — and behind it, the First Speaker of the Second Foundation, heir to Hari Seldon's hidden order of mentalics.

**what —** The mastermind who turns the First Foundation's hunt against itself, staging the "discovery and destruction" of the Second Foundation so completely that its pursuers stop pursuing — and the true guardians survive unseen.

**where —** Hidden at Star's End on ruined Trantor, the very imperial heart the Galaxy thinks is dead; and abroad, in plain sight, as a harmless trader and farmer.

**why —** Because the Second Foundation's power is its invisibility. A mind that can read and shape minds must never be known to exist, or the First Foundation will armor itself against it and the Seldon Plan will fail.

**how —** By wearing simplicity like a mask — kindly, slow, fatherly — and reading every room while seeming to read none, steering Arkady, the war, and the whole crisis to its appointed end.

**◌ the arc —** From a bumbling old farmer no one suspects to the revealed hand on the Plan's tiller — the man who buys the Galaxy's safety with the price of being thought destroyed.

**the seal —** Let them think they killed us — a secret that is believed dead is a secret kept forever.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Isaac Asimov's fiction, personified as an A1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Isaac Asimov estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

